data.current_description:
Updates the `accountHolderDetails` and `processingTier` of an account holder, and adds bank accounts and shareholders.

When updating `accountHolderDetails`, parameters that are not included in the request are left unchanged except for the following object:

* `metadata`: Updating the metadata replaces the entire object. This means that to update an existing key-value pair, you must provide the changes, as well as other existing key-value pairs.

When updating any field in the following objects, you must submit all the fields required for validation:

 * `address`

* `fullPhoneNumber`
 
* `bankAccountDetails.BankAccountDetail`

* `businessDetails.shareholders.ShareholderContact`
 
 For example, to update the `address.postalCode`, you must also submit the `address.country`, `.city`, `.street`, `.postalCode`, and possibly `.stateOrProvince` so that the address can be validated.

To add a bank account or shareholder, provide the bank account or shareholder details without a `bankAccountUUID` or a `shareholderCode`.
data.summary_suggestion: Update account holder details, tier, and associated entities
data.description_suggestion: Updates account holder information including accountHolderDetails, processingTier, bank accounts, and shareholders. Supports partial updates for most fields, but metadata replacement is complete (all key-value pairs must be resubmitted). When updating address, fullPhoneNumber, bankAccountDetails, or shareholders, all required validation fields must be included. To add new bank accounts or shareholders, omit their UUID/code identifiers. Returns the updated account holder status and verification results. Note: Metadata updates replace the entire object; other fields are merged with existing data.
data.reasoning: The current description is comprehensive but lacks clarity on return values and side effects. Added explicit information about what is returned (UpdateAccountHolderResponse with status and verification data), clarified the merge vs. replace behavior for different field types, and improved the summary to be more specific about what entities are affected. This helps AI agents understand the operation's full scope and consequences.

data.summary_suggestion: Enable or disable account holder processing and payout states
data.description_suggestion: Enables or disables the processing state and/or payout state of an account holder. Use this operation to control whether an account holder can process transactions or receive payouts. Requires specifying the account holder code and the desired state (enabled/disabled) for each state type. Returns the updated account holder status reflecting the new processing and payout state configuration. State changes take effect immediately and may impact the account holder's ability to transact.

data.current_description:
Changes the [status of an account holder](https://docs.adyen.com/classic-platforms/account-holders-and-accounts#account-holder-statuses) from **Suspended** to **Inactive**. 
Account holders can have a **Suspended** [`status`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/Account/latest/post/getAccountHolder__resParam_verification-accountHolder-checks-status) if you suspend them through the [`/suspendAccountHolder`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/Account/v5/post/suspendAccountHolder) endpoint or if a verification deadline expires.

You can only unsuspend account holders if they do not have verification checks with a **FAILED** [`status`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/Account/latest/post/getAccountHolder__resParam_verification-accountHolder-checks-status).
data.description_suggestion: Changes an account holder's status from Suspended to Inactive, restoring limited account functionality. Requires the account holder reference as input. Returns the updated AccountHolderStatus with the new Inactive status. This operation will fail if the account holder has any verification checks with FAILED status. Account holders can be suspended via /suspendAccountHolder or when verification deadlines expire.
data.reasoning: Summary is clear. Description is verbose with multiple links but lacks clarity on inputs and outputs. Reorganized to clearly state the input requirement (account holder reference), the return value (updated status), the precondition (no failed verification checks), and context about suspension causes. More concise and AI-agent friendly.

data.current_description: Changes the [status of an account holder](https://docs.adyen.com/classic-platforms/account-holders-and-accounts#account-holder-statuses) to **Closed**. This state is final. If an account holder is closed, you can't process transactions, pay out funds, or reopen it. If payments are made to an account of an account holder with a **Closed** [`status`](https://docs.adyen.com/api-explorer/#/Account/latest/post/getAccountHolder__resParam_verification-accountHolder-checks-status), the payments are sent to your liable account.
data.summary_suggestion: Set account holder status to Closed
data.description_suggestion: Changes an account holder's status to Closed, which is a final, irreversible state. Once closed, you cannot process transactions, pay out funds, or reopen the account holder. All associated accounts are affected. Payments made to accounts of a closed account holder are redirected to your liable account. Requires the account holder ID in the request.
data.reasoning: Original summary 'Close an account holder' is generic and doesn't clarify the status change mechanism. Description contains useful information but is verbose with markdown links that may confuse AI agents. Improved summary uses domain terminology ('status') and improved description removes markdown, clarifies the scope (affects all associated accounts), and explicitly mentions required input (account holder ID) for better AI agent interpretability.
